Title: Relates to the education and experience of members of the state board of parole
Summary: Relates to the education and experience of members of the state board of parole; provides that members can have either a degree and at least five years of experience in several fields or at least ten years of experience in such fields.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the executive law, in relation to the education and experience of members of the state board of parole
